Determine the rank of the following 3x3 matrix:

\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 2 & 3 \\ 4 & 5 & 6 \\ 7 & 8 & 9 \\ \end{bmatrix} 

What is the rank of this matrix?

message_2:
To determine the rank of the matrix, we need to perform Gaussian elimination to find the row echelon form of the matrix. Let's perform Gaussian elimination:

Original matrix:
\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 2 & 3 \\ 4 & 5 & 6 \\ 7 & 8 & 9 \\ \end{bmatrix}

Step 1: Subtract 4 times the first row from the second row, and subtract 7 times the first row from the third row:
\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 2 & 3 \\ 0 & -3 & -6 \\ 0 & -6 & -12 \\ \end{bmatrix}

Step 2: Divide the second row by -3:
\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 2 & 3 \\ 0 & 1 & 2 \\ 0 & -6 & -12 \\ \end{bmatrix}

Step 3: Add 6 times the second row to the third row:
\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 2 & 3 \\ 0 & 1 & 2 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 \\ \end{bmatrix}

The row echelon form of the matrix has two non-zero rows, so the rank of the matrix is 2.
